India Says Companies Need $20 Million to Issue Structured Debt

-- B y   A n u r a g   J o s h i
-- 
2011-09-29T05:44:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-29/india-says-companies-need-20-million-to-issue-structured-debt.html
Indian companies issuing structured
debt linked to exchange-traded derivatives need a net worth of
at least 1 billion rupees ($20 million), the Securities and
Exchange Board of India said.  The face value of “equity-linked debentures” should be a
minimum 1 million rupees, the market regulator known as SEBI
said in a statement posted on its website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anurag Joshi in Mumbai at 
